<ul>
<li><strong>To make this work:</strong>
<ul>
<li>Create a folder: <code>your-project/assets/my-gallery-assets/</code></li>
<li>Add images like <code>landscape.jpg</code>, <code>portrait.png</code>, <code>pano.webp</code> into that folder.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Captions generated</strong>: &ldquo;landscape&rdquo;, &ldquo;portrait&rdquo;, &ldquo;pano&rdquo;.</li>
<li><strong>Thumbnails</strong>: 300x300 smart-cropped versions will be generated.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="2-gallery-with-local-images-from-static">2. Gallery with Local Images from <code>/static</code><a href="#2-gallery-with-local-images-from-static" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"
      stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="feather">
      <path d="M15 7h3a5 5 0 0 1 5 5 5 5 0 0 1-5 5h-3m-6 0H6a5 5 0 0 1-5-5 5 5 0 0 1 5-5h3"></path>
      <line x1="8" y1="12" x2="16" y2="12"></line>
   </svg></a></h3>
<p>Place your images inside the <code>/static</code> directory. For instance, if you have images in <code>/static/event-photos/</code>:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"><code class="language-markdown" data-lang="markdown"><span style="display:flex;"><span>{{&lt; gallery &gt;}}
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>/event-photos/conference.jpg
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>/event-photos/workshop.jpeg
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>{{&lt; /gallery &gt;}}
